OL,3,CLindsey Burrow: Who Cares For Our
OL,4,CCarers?
OL,6,FWe'll meet carers like Sue, a 71-year-
OL,7,Fold unpaid carer who lives with her
OL,8,Felderly Mum and husband who was
OL,9,Frecently diagnosed with dementia.
OL,10,FDespite retiring years ago, Sue is
OL,11,Fbusier than ever balancing care for
OL,12,Ftwo loved ones.
OL,14,FBut carers like Sue can't always get a
OL,15,Fbreak. Recent research suggests only 1
OL,16,Fout of 142 carers receive any respite
OL,17,Fcare, a fall of just over 40% since
OL,18,F2015.
