OL,3,CLindsey Burrow: Who Cares For Our
OL,4,CCarers?
OL,6,FOther carers are feeling the squeeze
OL,7,Fof the cost of living crisis. Michael
OL,8,Fis an unpaid carer for his 29-year-old
OL,9,Fdaughter Suzie who has been severely
OL,10,Fdisabled since birth. He claims
OL,11,Fcarer's allowance and other benefits
OL,12,Fbut he says he struggles to make ends
OL,13,Fmeet.
OL,15,FOn average 600 people a day leave work
OL,16,Fto care for others, and according to
OL,17,Fthe Joseph Rowntree foundation, 44% of
OL,18,Fworking age adults who care are in
OL,19,Fpoverty.
